  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p>This is the first entry. Mostly to confirm the deploy pipeline works.</p>
<section id="what-lives-here" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="what-lives-here">What lives here</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Long-form notes</strong> on projects I’m building — design decisions, benchmarks, and the reasoning behind the choices.</li>
<li><strong>Short posts</strong> on tooling, libraries, and patterns that turned out to be load-bearing.</li>
<li><strong>Project pages</strong> that point at the code and summarize what the project is, what worked, and what didn’t.</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="what-doesnt" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="what-doesnt">What doesn’t</h2>
<p>Polished tutorials, opinion pieces unrelated to engineering, and anything that would be better as a tweet.</p>
</section>
<section id="how-posts-are-organized" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="how-posts-are-organized">How posts are organized</h2>
<p>Each post lives in its own folder under <code>posts/</code>, which lets me colocate figures, notebooks, and supporting files with the prose. The site is built with <a href="https://quarto.org">Quarto</a> and rendered on push by GitHub Actions.</p>
